text: Olmedo (S'Ulumèdu, Urumèddu) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sassari in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 4,161 people lived there. Its area is 33.47 km². It is 68 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of Sassari
title: Olmedo
